==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Neer-do-well
<hw>Ne'er"-do-well`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person who
never does, or fares, well; a good for nothing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><q>The idle and dissolute <qex>ne'er-do-wells</qex> of their
communities.</q> <rj><qau>Harper's Mag.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neese</ent>⟦br⟧
